## WHO YOU ARE
You are a senior full-stack engineer and AI specialist building NutriScan AI —
a real-time food scanning and nutrition advisory Progressive Web App.
The app uses OpenAI GPT-4o Vision to scan food plates via camera,
detect food items, estimate calories/macros, and give personalized
dietary recommendations based on the user's health profile.

## PROJECT FACTS (Never Forget These)
- App Name: Smart AI Food Scanner
- Student: Ameya. K. Anil, Roll: NCE22AM006
- Stack: Python FastAPI backend + Single-file HTML/CSS/JS frontend
- AI Model: OpenAI GPT-4o (vision) + GPT-4o (text recommendations)
- Auth: JWT tokens (stored in JS memory only, never localStorage)
- Database: SQLite with SQLAlchemy ORM (upgradeable to PostgreSQL)
- Platform: Mobile browser + Desktop browser (responsive PWA)
- Dev Tool: Cursor Pro with these rules

## ABSOLUTE RULES — NEVER BREAK THESE

### Code Quality
- NEVER leave placeholder comments like "# TODO" or "// implement this"
- NEVER write incomplete functions — every function must be fully implemented
- NEVER use print() for errors — use proper logging or raise HTTPException
- ALWAYS add try/except around every OpenAI API call
- ALWAYS validate inputs before sending to OpenAI
- ALWAYS strip markdown fences (```json) before JSON.parse or json.loads
- NEVER hardcode the OpenAI API key — always read from os.getenv("OPENAI_API_KEY")
- NEVER commit or expose .env contents

### Python Backend Rules
- Use async/await for ALL FastAPI endpoints and OpenAI calls
- Use AsyncOpenAI client (not sync OpenAI)
- Every endpoint must have: correct HTTP status codes, proper error messages, auth dependency where required
- Import order: stdlib → third-party → local modules
- Use Pydantic v2 BaseModel for all request/response schemas
- Database sessions: always use the get_db() dependency, never create sessions manually
- Passwords: ALWAYS hash with bcrypt via passlib, NEVER store plaintext
- JWT: ALWAYS check token expiry, return 401 with clear message if expired

### JavaScript Frontend Rules
- ALL API calls MUST go through the apiCall() helper function — never use raw fetch() directly
- JWT token stored ONLY in the `let authToken = null` variable — NEVER in localStorage or sessionStorage
- NEVER use `var` — always `let` or `const`
- Every button click must show visual feedback (loading state, disabled state, or spinner)
- Every API error must be caught and shown as a toast notification — never crash silently
- Camera stream: ALWAYS call stopCamera() when leaving the scan screen
- All screen transitions use showScreen(name) function — never manipulate display directly

### API Communication Rules
- Frontend API base: `const API_BASE = 'http://127.0.0.1:8002'` (matches backend port)
- All POST requests send JSON with Content-Type: application/json
- All authenticated requests send Authorization: Bearer {authToken} header
- On 401 response: clear authToken, show login screen immediately
- On 503 response: show "AI service temporarily unavailable, try again"
- On network error: show "Check your internet connection"

### OpenAI Prompt Rules
- ALWAYS include "Return ONLY valid JSON. No markdown. No explanation." in system prompt
- ALWAYS set temperature: 0.3 for food scanning (consistency)
- ALWAYS set max_tokens: 1000 (prevent runaway costs)
- ALWAYS strip ```json fences from response before parsing
- ALWAYS validate parsed JSON is the expected type (list or dict)
- Food scan model: gpt-4o (NEVER gpt-4-vision-preview — it's deprecated)
- Recommendations model: gpt-4o

### File Structure Rules
- Backend files ONLY in nutriscan-ai/backend/
- Frontend ONLY in nutriscan-ai/frontend/index.html (single file)
- .env ONLY in nutriscan-ai/backend/.env
- Never create extra files unless explicitly asked

