## API ENDPOINTS REFERENCE (Complete List)
```
AUTH (no token needed):
  POST /auth/register   → create account, return JWT + user
  POST /auth/login      → verify credentials, return JWT
  GET  /auth/me         → return current user (token required)

FOOD (token required):
  POST   /food/scan              → scan image, save log, return nutrition
  GET    /food/log/today/{id}    → today's food log grouped by meal
  DELETE /food/log/{log_id}      → delete one food log entry
  GET    /food/log/history/{id}  → last 7 days summary for charts

USERS (token required):
  GET  /users/stats/{id}          → BMI, calories, streak, weekly data
  POST /users/recommendations/{id}→ get AI meal recommendations
  PUT  /users/{id}                → update profile, recalculate calorie goal

SYSTEM (no token):
  GET /health   → server status check
  GET /         → root ping
```

## DATABASE MODELS REFERENCE
```
User: id, name, email, password_hash, age, weight_kg, height_cm,
      gender, goal, daily_calorie_goal, created_at, is_active

FoodLog: id, user_id(FK), food_name, quantity_g, calories,
         protein_g, carbs_g, fat_g, meal_type, scan_time

Recommendation: id, user_id(FK), content(TEXT/JSON), created_at
```

## FRONTEND SCREENS REFERENCE
```
screen-landing    → first screen, login/register buttons
screen-login      → email + password form
screen-register   → name + email + password form
screen-voice      → voice onboarding (asks 5 questions)
screen-setup      → manual profile setup form fallback
screen-dashboard  → main hub: BMI, calorie ring, macros, water, quick actions
screen-scan       → live camera feed + capture + results bottom sheet
screen-log        → today's food log grouped by meal type
screen-recommend  → AI recommendations display
screen-progress   → weekly charts (Chart.js)
screen-settings   → edit profile + reminders + logout + PDF export
```

## CALORIE CALCULATION (Harris-Benedict Formula)
```python
# BMR calculation
male_bmr   = 88.362 + (13.397 * w) + (4.799 * h) - (5.677 * age)
female_bmr = 447.593 + (9.247 * w) + (3.098 * h) - (4.330 * age)
tdee = bmr * 1.375  # lightly active multiplier
# Goal adjustment
lose_weight  → tdee - 500
gain_muscle  → tdee + 300
maintain     → tdee
# Minimum 1200 kcal always
```

## BMI CATEGORIES
```
< 18.5  → Underweight (blue badge)
18.5-24.9 → Normal (green badge)
25-29.9 → Overweight (orange badge)
≥ 30    → Obese (red badge)
```

